com.arcrobotics.ftclib.geometry

Class Vector2d

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.arcrobotics.ftclib.geometry.Vector2d

  • public class Vector2d
extends java.lang.Object
    Think of a vector as a ray with a starting point at the origin. The point represented by (x, y) is the point that the ray's arrow points. This represents the vector in 2d Cartesian space. A vector is essentially a value, or magnitude, with a set direction. You can also put a vector in polar form: (r, theta), where r is the magnitude and theta is the directional angle.
